bstracting away return types behind `Result`, hiding COM lifetime management, etc).\r\n\r\nThe choice for the \"heavier\" `windows` crate over `windows-sys` is fairly obvious: DirectX APIs are built on the COM object model which is completely unsupported in `windows-sys` making us unable to perform any method calls.  Besides, the `windows-sys` crate does very little to make the API more convenient nor safer to use, effectively taking us a step back from `winapi` instead of a step forward.", "created_at": "2022-03-24T22:58:53Z", "updated_at": "2022-05-19T12:00:13Z", "closed_at": "2022-05-19T12:00:05Z", "merged_at": "2022-05-19T12:00:05Z", "merge_commit_sha": "dae232e1b6e91a4eca99215811639dad63befb4c", "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "requested_reviewers": [], "requested_teams": [], "labels": [], "milestone": null, "draft": false, "commits_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Traverse-Research/gpu-allocator/pulls/107/commits", "review_comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Traverse-Research/gpu-allocator/pulls/107/comments", "review_comment_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Traverse-Research/gpu-allocator/pulls/comments{/number}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Traverse-Research/gpu-allocator/issues/107/comments", "statuses_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Traverse-Research/gpu-allocator/statuses/de4a191dcbc31f5af7ea63f6a776aecc48bc7f7d", "head": {"label": "Traverse-Research:windows-rs", "ref": "windows-rs", "sha": "de4a191dcbc31f5af7ea63f6a776aecc48bc7f7d", "user": {"login": "Traverse-Research", "id": 60381534, "node_id": "MDEyOk9yZ2FuaXphdGlvbjYwMzgxNTM0", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/60381534?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/Traverse-Research", "html_url": "https://github.com/Traverse-Research", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Traverse-Research/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Traverse-Research/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://ap